This is a [keeba](https://github.com/aomerk/keeba)-managed wiki.

## How to use it

```bash
keeba lint              # check the wiki against SCHEMA.md
keeba drift             # verify code citations are still in bounds
keeba meta              # rebuild the agent-facing _meta.json + _xref/
keeba search "query"    # BM25 search over the wiki
keeba mcp serve         # stdio MCP server (for Claude Code, Cursor, Codex)
```

## Layout

- [`index.md`](index.md) — entry point for both humans and agents.
- [`SCHEMA.md`](SCHEMA.md) — what every page must contain.
- [`log.md`](log.md) — append-only activity log.
- `entities/`, `concepts/`, `investigations/`, `decisions/` — the actual pages.
- `agents/` — Markdown prompt templates for ingest agents.
- `_meta.json`, `_xref/` — generated; `keeba meta` rebuilds them.

## Editing

Pages must follow [`SCHEMA.md`](SCHEMA.md). Run `keeba lint --staged` before
committing to catch violations locally. CI runs the same lint on every PR.

